5D6B43D3.Line1.F738D: No, I’m not all right! Just look at the color of her bark, the poor Tree. My chanting is the only thing keeping her upright.

727627E4.Line11.F738D: I’d search that darkness myself, but I can’t leave her side. Please... help me save her?

C53D29DB.Line9.F738D: She needs a piece of her mother – the Great Oak of Túr Dúlra. Got to go deep for it, though... down to the Underroot where the Ancients first planted.

CC74AA00.VoiceDir1.F738D: Worried. Exhausted. Heavy with his responsibility for this sacred, currently dying tree.
